          "The second sum is exact: $\\tfrac1{n^2}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}k=\\tfrac{n(n+1)}{2n^2}=\\tfrac{n+1}{2n}\\to\\tfrac12=\\int_0^1 x\\,dx$.",
          "Hence $\\ln L=\\int_0^1\\ln x\\,dx+\\int_0^1 x\\,dx=-1+\\tfrac12=-\\tfrac12$, so $L=e^{-1/2}=\\boxed{\\dfrac{1}{\\sqrt{e}}}$."
