          "Hence $\\sin(\\pi a^n)=\\sin\\!\\big(-\\pi b^n+\\pi N_n\\big)$; the parity of $N_n$ (always even) makes this $-\\sin(\\pi b^n)$, with $\\sin(\\pi b^n)=\\pi b^n+O(b^{3n})$.",
