          "Inductive step. Assume $a_n=2\\cos\\tfrac{\\pi}{2^{n+1}}$. Using $2+2\\cos\\theta=4\\cos^2\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}$ with $\\theta=\\tfrac{\\pi}{2^{n+1}}$ (so $\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}=\\tfrac{\\pi}{2^{n+2}}$ stays in $(0,\\tfrac{\\pi}{2})$, where cosine is positive):",
